<title>UK: UK major bank mortgage lending rises in Feb - BBA.</title>
<headline>UK major bank mortgage lending rises in Feb - BBA.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-04-01</dateline>
<text>
<p>The British Bankers Association</p>
<p>released the following data on major banking groups' gross and</p>
<p>net lending in February.</p>
<p>(in millions of stg unless otherwise stated)</p>
<p> Period	     net lending(s/a)  gross lending</p>
<p> February	   +743		  +2,153</p>
<p> January	    +806		  +2,085</p>
<p>NOTES - (s/a) = seasonally adjusted. The BBA said while lending was not as buoyant as January, the major banks' net mortgage lending in February was significantly above the recently monthly average.</p>
</text>
